HEADWORD: Nacarat
<hw>Nac"a*rat</hw> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧k"⟦adot⟧*r⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>nacarat</ets>, fr. Sp. or Pg. <ets>nacarado</ets>, fr.
<ets>n⟦aacute⟧car</ets> mother-of-pearl. See <er>Nacre</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A pale red color, with a cast of orange.</def>
